other_tests.findings: Laparoscopic exploration revealed testicular vessels leading into the inguinal canals on both sides. Further laparoscopic groin exploration identified atrophic testes in the groin canals.
Histological examination of the excised testes showed atrophic seminiferous tubules with only Sertoli cells apparent. Germ cells were large and atypical with nuclear atypia and clear cytoplasm.

Immunohistochemical staining of germ cells showed weak positivity for CD117 and SALL4, indicating maturation arrest of spermatogenesis and germ cell neoplasia in situ (GCNIS) in bilateral testes. Staining for testosterone-synthesizing enzymes was negative, while staining for Ad4BP/SF-1 was positive.
